OL,3,CDeath of Baby Ida proof of 'systemic'
OL,4,Cfailings in maternity care
OL,6,FHis report was published in March
OL,7,F2015, and found a "lethal mix" of
OL,8,Ffailures that led to the deaths of 11
OL,9,Fbabies and a mother at the trust.
OL,11,FFour years on from the report being
OL,12,Fpublished, Ida Lock was born at the
OL,13,FRoyal Lancaster Infirmary but she died
OL,14,Fjust six days later after suffering a
OL,15,Fserious brain injury.
OL,17,FWhile an initial investigation from
OL,18,Fthe trust found no failures in her
OL,19,Fdelivery, an independent review
OL,20,Fdiscovered a number of shortcomings
OL,21,Ffrom midwives and medical staff.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/14
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
