OL,3,CDeath of Baby Ida proof of 'systemic'
OL,4,Cfailings in maternity care
OL,6,FYet when Dr Kirkup gave evidence at
OL,7,Fthe inquest, he told the coroner that
OL,8,Fthere was evidence to suggest this was
OL,9,Fstill the case in 2019, and that
OL,10,Fhospital staff were needlessly
OL,11,Fdefensive when it came to admitting
OL,12,Fmistakes out of fear of punishment.
OL,14,FAfter the inquest, he said: "What we
OL,15,Fshouldn't be doing is blaming people
OL,16,Ffor clinical errors. They're a fact of
OL,17,Flife, but you have to respond to them,
OL,18,Fbe open about them, and properly
OL,19,Finvestigate them to make sure they
OL,20,Fdon't happen again.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/14
