OL,3,CDeath of Baby Ida proof of 'systemic'
OL,4,Cfailings in maternity care
OL,6,FHe also said: "It is apparent from the
OL,7,Fevidence of Dr Kirkup and the
OL,8,Fincreasing number of enquiries into
OL,9,Fsignificant shortcomings in maternity
OL,10,Funits, that this is a national issue."
OL,12,FIn his conclusion, Dr James Adeley
OL,13,Fsaid he would be filing a Prevent
OL,14,FFuture Deaths report and agreed that
OL,15,Fthe failings in this case "would
OL,16,Findicate a dysfunction that is
OL,17,Fgenuinely identifiable as systemic".
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G11/14
